OPENSYNC SYNCML CLIENT PLUGIN README
====================================

This is a SyncML client plugin based on the SyncML C++ API from 
http://www.funambol.org. The plugin can synchronize contacts, calendars,
notes and todos.

Configuration follows the usual opensync procedure. Here's an example how
to create a synchronization group with sync4j and file-sync:

$ msynctool --addgroup sync4jfile
$ msynctool --addmember sync4jfile syncml-client
$ msynctool --addmember sync4jfile file-sync
$ msynctool --configure sync4jfile 1

This will open an editor and you are required to set some minimal settings (most
are already set to a reasonable default value).
In node <Auth> set your credentials.
In node <Conn> set the url.
In node <Sources> adapt <uri> to point to the correct database.

$ msynctool --configure sync4jfile 1
Configure the file-sync plugin

$ msynctool --discover sync4jfile 1
$ msynctool --discover sync4jfile 2

Now make a sync
$ msynctool --sync sync4jfile




